uld not have been able to continu=\r\ne the spiritual practices which he was already doing for some time, and lea=\r\nving something half way is not good.\n\n\nReading the explanation your provide=\r\nd below, that is : \n\n&quot;We meditate upon that Savitaa (yaH) who impels (prach=\r\nodayaat) our (naH) \nthoughts (dhiyaH). He blesses us with subtle eyesight. =\r\nWithout his \nlight, we would not be able to distinguish different objects. =\r\nThis is \nexplained in the Aitaterya Upanishad=C2=A0=E2=80=9CThe sun, having=\r\n become eyesight, \nentered the eyes=E2=80=9D. He thus blesses all living be=\r\nings.&quot;\n\n.. matches with the description that I had heard from my friend. Qu=\r\nite interesting!\n\n-Regards\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n\n\n\n\n=C2=A0\n\nawaktam wyaktimApanna=\r\nm manyantE mAmabuddhayah |\nparam bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24=\r\n]\n\n\n________________________________\n From: &quot;ajit.krishnan@...&quot; &lt;ajit=\r\n.krishnan@...&gt;\nTo: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoo=\r\ngroups.com&gt; \nSent: Monday, 7 January 2013 11:39 AM\nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] =\r\nGayatri -- Savita\n \n\n=C2=A0 \nNamaste,\n=C2=A0\nPainganadu Ganapati Shastri wa=\r\ns a=C2=A0well known=C2=A0aasthaana vidvaan=C2=A0of the Kanchi Peetham. He w=\r\nrote a simple, lucid commentary on the Gayatri mantra. It starts with a sum=\r\nmary in 32 shlokas, followed by an introduction. He then gives 4 explanatio=\r\nns / meditations on the mantra -- (1) gayatri, (2) narayana, (3) paramashiv=\r\na and (4) paramatma.\n=C2=A0\nI am not attempting a literal or scholarly tran=\r\nslation ... I=E2=80=99ll try to summarize the main point, from a practical =\r\npoint of view. I=E2=80=99ll start with the first of the meditations, on Gay=\r\natri.\n=C2=A0\n=C2=A0----\n=C2=A0\nThe first meditation is the=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cco=\r\nmmon=E2=80=9D understanding of the Gayatri mantra, with the Sun as the deva=\r\nta. This follows the famous verse from the Agastya 